Were amazed by the cinematic animation, and appreciate the sleep timer that sends Crumbs to bed when our kids screen time is over.

editorialNotes.standard: Bursting with beats and energy, Toca Dance will make the whole family want to get up and groove. This incredibly cute game puts kids in charge of their own musical productionchoosing dancers, costumes, and techno tracks, and choreographing moves using simple swipes and taps. Once the performance starts, the real fun begins: you can fling items at the stage, set off pyrotechnics and other cool effects, and even cheer (or boo) your squad. Seeing the payoffan awesome video you can sharewill encourage players to jump right back in and start working on their next great show.

editorialNotes.standard: See the beauty and power of ABCs in an app where every letter holds secret words. Touch an F, and it sprouts a foot, then feathers, then a fan; a G becomes a guitar in a garden with ghosts. Kids will love poking and prodding their way to the end of the alphabet, while parents will dig the unpredictability and gorgeous animation in this Apple Design Award winner.
editorialNotes.short: Interactive alphabet learning where words and letters come to life.

Kids (and kids at heart) can unleash their inner scientists with this captivatingly clever robot-creation kit, which features millions of different combinations for mechanical inventions. Whether youre assembling a wheeled bot with laser guns for arms or a jolly jumping automaton with pogo-stick legs, taking your new bot on a walk through the woods will highlight the successor the rough edgesof your design. While The Robot Factory teaches some nifty physics basics, we like to play around just for the pure fun of it.
editorialNotes.short: Design and experiment with all types of robots.

editorialNotes.standard: In this imaginative animated storybook, two of Sesame Streets most popular characters team up to spark your childs love of reading. As fearful Grover concocts hilarious obstacles to keep kids from reaching the last page, eager Elmo asks for their help to discover the mysterious monster at the end of the story. Its an engaging experience that teaches bravery and conflict resolution through lively interactivity, adorable artwork, and heartwarming humor. Parental tips help you integrate these lessons during storytime and beyond, combining learning and play with practical advice from a name you can trust.

Part digital toy and part planetary handbook, The Earth gives kids insight into the workings of our world in a way thats delightfully intuitive and fun. From rockslides to earthquakes to erupting volcanoes, these artful interactive dioramas respond to tapping and swiping with results that are both whimsical and educational. An accompanying guide for parents and teachers delves into the technical science behind all these phenomena, but kids can explore, experiment, and absorb earthly knowledge at their own pace.
editorialNotes.short: Play with interactive models to understand our planet.

editorialNotes.standard: Slide a shape into the correct holeeasy, right? It is, at first. But what makes Busy Shapes so clever is the way it gently gets more challenging, motivating little kids to find solutions to each puzzle through experimentation. From shape-changing to color-mixing to hidden holes, were impressed with how the gameplay spurs out-of-the-box thinking, stimulating curious young minds.
